we can use Atom editor to create a prototype of Comshell;

; sudo pacman -S atom sway xorg-server-xwayland
; nano ~/.bash_profile
  sway
; mkdir -p ~/.config/sway
; nano ~/.config/sway/config
  default_border none
  focus_follows_mouse no
  for_window [class=Atom] floating enable, \
    resize set 100 ppt 100 ppt, move position center
  exec --no-startup-id "atom --wait; i3-msg exit"
; cp Atom/* ~/.atom/

native Launcher: rework Atom startup process by introducing a dedicated native executable that checks for a running Atom application and boots one up if needed;

for treeview define a new command (and bind it) which first checks
  if the entry is a directory containing a ".gallery" file,
  if so, open gallery, if not, call the actual command;
atom.workspace.addOpener(uri => ...)
  if uri is a directory containing a ".gallery" file
    return the model for gallery view implementing ".getPath()"

